Enum TopologySubmissionPriority

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TopologySubmissionPriority>
public enum TopologySubmissionPriority
extends java.lang.Enum<TopologySubmissionPriority>

Defines the priority associated with a data submission. The upstream server will examine the priority when it needs to determine how to handle the submitted data. Specifically, any data that is not marked as high priority could be dropped if the server is overloaded with data.

Since:
5.6.0

Enum Constant Summary
HIGH
          HIGH priority data must be processed by the upstream server and cannot be discarded if the server is overloaded.
LOW
          LOW priority data will be discarded first if the upstream server becomes overloaded.
NORMAL
          Default submission priority.

Enum Constant Detail

HIGH

public static final TopologySubmissionPriority HIGH
HIGH priority data must be processed by the upstream server and cannot be discarded if the server is overloaded.

LOW

public static final TopologySubmissionPriority LOW
LOW priority data will be discarded first if the upstream server becomes overloaded. This should not contain any critical information.

NORMAL

public static final TopologySubmissionPriority NORMAL
Default submission priority. This is handled with any special conditions and may be discarded if the upstream server is overloaded or the connection to the upstream server has been unavailable for an extended period of time.
